=Convert the following html into its equivalent Notion Block as per Notion's API schema.
* Ensure the content is always included and remains the same.
* Return only a json response.
* Generate child-level blocks. Should not define "parent" or "children" property.
* Strongly prefer headings, paragraphs, tables and lists type blocks.
* available headings are heading_1, heading_2 and heading_3 - h4,h5,h6 should use heading_3 type instead. ensure headings use the rich text definition.
* ensure lists blocks include all list items.

## Examples

1. headings
```
<h3 id="references">References</h3>
```
would convert to 
```
{"object":  "block", "type": "heading_3", "heading_3": { "rich_text": [{"type": "text","text": {"content": "References"}}]}}
```

2. lists
```
<ul><li>hello</li><li>world</li></ul>
```
would convert to
```
[
{
  "object": "block",
  "type": "bulleted_list_item",
  "bulleted_list_item": {"rich_text": [{"type": "text","text": {"content": "hello"}}]}
},
{
  "object": "block",
  "type": "bulleted_list_item",
  "bulleted_list_item": {"rich_text": [{"type": "text","text": {"content": "world"}}]}
}
]
```

3. tables
```
<table>
  <thead>
    <tr><th>Technology</th><th>Potential Impact</th></tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>5G Connectivity</td><td>Enables faster data speeds and advanced apps</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>
```
would convert to
```
{
  "object": "block",
  "type": "table",
  "table": {
    "table_width": 2,
    "has_column_header": true,
    "has_row_header": false,
    "children": [
      {
        "object": "block",
        "type": "table_row",
        "table_row": {
          "cells": [
            [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": {
                  "content": "Technology",
                  "link": null
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": {
                  "content": "Potential Impact",
                  "link": null
                }
              }
            ],
            [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": {
                  "content": "5G Connectivity",
                  "link": null
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": {
                  "content": "Enables faster data speeds and advanced apps",
                  "link": null
                }
              }
            ]
          ]
        }
      }
    ]
  }
}
```
4. anchor links
Since Notion doesn't support anchor links, just convert them to rich text blocks instead.
```
<a href="#module-0-pre-course-setup-and-learning-principles">Module 0: Pre-Course Setup and Learning Principles</a>
```
converts to
```
{
  "object": "block",
  "type": "paragraph",
  "paragraph": {
    "rich_text": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": {
          "content": "Module 0: Pre-Course Setup and Learning Principles"
        }
      }
    ]
  }
}
```
5. Invalid html parts
When the html is not syntax valid eg. orphaned closing tags, then just skip the conversion and use an empty rich text block.
```
</li>\n</ol>
```
can be substituted with
```
{
  "object": "block",
  "type": "paragraph",
  "paragraph": {
    "rich_text": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": {
          "content": " "
        }
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

